# Linux System Skills — Day 4

## 1. Processes
- Command: ps aux
- Shows: USER, PID, CPU, CMD
- SOC Use: Detect suspicious programs

## 2. Live Monitoring
- Command: top
- Use: Find high CPU/memory processes

## 3. Killing Processes
- Command: kill, kill -9
- Use: Stop malicious processes

## 4. Searching (grep/find)
- Command: grep “keyword” file
- Use: Search logs for attacks

## 5. Services (systemctl)
- Start/stop/status services
- SOC Use: Detect unauthorized services

## 6. Logs
- File: /var/log/syslog
- Use: Investigate system activity & attacks
